# mod_GLQS_readme
*clr & cla
'<b>Version 0.29.4 - Current</b>'
'- Note: Fame By Region - Max All (this region) only sets that regions own fame directly, but the games own fame-spread system then bleeds some of that into the other regions too (working as designed - e.g. maxing Pavlovsk also pushes Old Town and Gadukino close to maxed, since fame spreads fast between those, while City only gets a small bump since it is slow to notice fame from Pavlovsk). This is base game behavior, not a mod bug.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.3</b>'
'- Fixed: Relationships menu threw a Bracket not found error on open. The v0.29.2 refactor built the NPC value cell as a template marker split across a string concatenation, which QSP does not allow. Now reads npc_rel directly as a value instead of through a template marker.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.2</b>'
'- Changed: Internal refactor, no player-visible change. Relationships (roster + category maxing) and the clothing store catalog (store_buy and the Give Everything handler) each used to hardcode the same NPC list or store/category list in two or three places; they now share one data table each, looped over at render/apply time, so the copies can no longer drift out of sync.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29.1</b>'
'- Added: Store icon shown at the top of the store category list and the item picker screen.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.29</b>'
'- Changed: Clothing categories (e.g. Allure - Swimsuits) now open an image grid like the tattoo/piercing pickers instead of instantly buying every item in the category. Click an item to add just that one, or use Give All (this category) to still buy the whole category in one click.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28.2</b>'
'- Changed: Updated the mod description (shown in the games mod list) to cover everything GLQS actually does now - money, relationships, health, body mods and fame were missing from it.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28.1</b>'
'- Changed: Removed Return to Top Menu from the tattoo design screen (Body Mods, Choose a Tattoo, pick a zone) - Back to Zones already covers it at that depth.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.28</b>'
'- Fixed: Fame By Region (individual activity buttons, Max All This Region, and the live table) still did not apply. Root cause: the region code was captured from ARGS after calling stat/themes, which clobber the shared ARGS array just like any nested gs call, and a stray killvar was clearing the captured region before the player could click a button. Same fix applied to the clothing per-store screen and the tattoo/piercing pickers, which had the same latent bug.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.27</b>'
'- Fixed: Fame maxing (individual activity, Max All This Region, Max All Fame) silently did nothing and the live table always read 0. Root cause: same ARGS clobbering bug as the v0.7 grades fix - re-reading ARGS after a nested gs call back into mod_GLQS_main picked up the callees ARGS instead. Fixed by capturing region/activity into local variables before any nested call.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.26</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation now shows live values - a per-region overview table (Performer, Sex Industry, Slut/Sex Rep, Sport) on the region picker, and a full per-activity fame table on each region screen, matching the Skills & Attributes style.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.25</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation submenu now has a By Region breakdown (Pavlovsk, City, Old Town, Gadukino) with an individual Max button per activity, plus a Max All (this region) option, alongside the existing Max All Fame (everything) button.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.24</b>'
'- Added: Fame & Reputation submenu with a Max All Fame button covering every activity (acting, dance, painting, music, ballet, modelling, porn, stripping, kickboxing, running, volleyball, chess, teaching, media, sex, prostitution, flashing) across all four regions.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.23</b>'
'- Added: Every submenu now has a Return to Top Menu button that jumps straight back to the main Quick Setup screen, in addition to any existing one-level-back navigation.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.22</b>'
'- Added: Buy By Store submenu now breaks each store down into individual category buttons (e.g. Panties, Bras, Outfits, Shoes) instead of one buy-everything action, plus a Buy All (this store) option.'
'- Fixed: Store category submenu used single-line if statements with a trailing end, which QSP does not allow - it desynced block parsing for the rest of mod_GLQS_main and caused an Unknown action error. Removed the invalid end from every single-line if.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.21</b>'
'- Added: Per-category [Max] link next to each relationship category header (Family, Popular Kids, Athletes, Nerds, Gopniks, Outcasts, Teachers, Others), respecting the gender filter.'
'- Changed: Tattoo/piercing image galleries now use a wrapping grid layout instead of stacking vertically.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.20</b>'
'- Changed: Body Mods now lets you pick a zone/slot and browse actual tattoo and piercing designs by image, instead of a single Give All button. Electrolysis unchanged.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.19</b>'
'- Fixed: Apostrophes inside !! comments (e.g. games, cheat_repair) broke the parser - the game engine does not fully suppress quote-parsing inside comments, so a lone apostrophe opened an unterminated string that corrupted all block-nesting after it. Removed all apostrophes from comments.'
'- Changed: Individual store buttons in Clothing & Accessories moved behind a Buy By Store submenu.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.18</b>'
'- Added: Per-store buy-out buttons in Clothing & Accessories.'
'- Fixed: Clothing no longer needs tailor repair/resize. Root cause was the companion _h[] durability array never being set, defaulting to 0.'
'- Added: Body Mods submenu (free electrolysis, tattoo every zone, piercing every slot).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.17</b>'
'- Added: Money submenu (open bank account, give cash/bank funds).'
'- Added: Relationships submenu showing and maxing key NPC relationships.'
'- Added: Health & Energy submenu with full restore.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.16.1</b>'
'- Added: Consumables submenu now has Set All to 10,000 / 1,000 / 100 options.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.15</b>'
'- Removed: Do Everything option.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.14</b>'
'- Fixed: Max All Skills & Attributes was redirecting to the cheat menu. setSkills and setAttrs both end with gt cheatmenu_din which hijacks navigation. Replaced with direct setStat calls for every skill and attribute.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.13</b>'
'- Added: Clothing, Consumables and Skills & Attributes all now open their own submenus showing live data before applying changes.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.12</b>'
'- Changed: Grades moved to its own submenu showing live grade values.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.11</b>'
'- Fixed: Grades re-added. Root cause: grade_cap=0 clamped all grade_award calls to 0 in nested gs context. Fixed with 13 flat direct calls.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.9</b>'
'- Fixed: Consumables completely rewritten using correct mc_inventory[''name''] system.'
'- All old variable names (prezikcount, tampon, etc.) were legacy/wrong - replaced with 67 correct mc_inventory keys.'
'- Added full coverage: beauty, medical, contraceptives, drugs, food, sex toys, magazines, unique equipment.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.8</b>'
'- Dropped: Grades support removed. The grade system requires school initialization (createclass/grade_cap) that cannot be reliably set from a mod context.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.7</b>'
'- Fixed: Grade variables now set class cap to 100 before assigning grade directly.'
'- Fixed: ARGS[1] was being clobbered by inner gs calls inside fill_grade loop.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.6</b>'
'- Fixed: Syntax error caused by inline !! comments after code (QSP only supports !! at start of a line).'
'- Fixed: Em dash characters in comments caused parser crash.'
'- Fixed: Attributes now use gs ''shortgs'', ''setStat'' directly (setAttrs needed $att_name[] pre-populated at startup).'
'- Fixed: Grade storage uses class[''school_X_grade''] not gschoolVars. Grades are 0-100 not 1-5.'
'- Fixed: Inhibition raw value is inverted - 100 = uninhibited, 0 = fully inhibited.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.5</b>'
'- Fixed: Inline !! comments partially addressed. Attribute variable names corrected from game source.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.4</b>'
'- Fixed: Skill and attribute variable names corrected using cheatmenu_din source code.'
'- Added: Skills, attributes and grades option (grades still broken at this point).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.3</b>'
'- Added: Max Skills / Attributes / Grades option (all variable names wrong, fixed in later versions).'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.2</b>'
'- Fixed: Clothing now unlocks from ALL stores, not just visited ones.'
'- Root cause: arrsize() returns 0 for unvisited store arrays. Fixed by using each category totals subroutine.'
*nl
'<b>Version 0.1 - Initial Release</b>'
'- All clothing and accessories from every store.'
'- 10,000 of all consumables (variable names were wrong, fixed in 0.9).'
*nl
act 'Return': gt 'mod_setting'
--- mod_GLQS_readme ---------------------------------
